@minrk I've been playing with the idea of an API in which you have a decorator that accepts [`TraitEventHandler`](https://github.com/rmorshea/traitlets/blob/b4c913192842f5e6610f8177e88041edd1a93fd6/traitlets/traitlets.py#L914-L948) instances in order to install itself as a sort or generic callback. For example:

```python

class A(HasTraits):

	i = Int()
	j = Int()
	
	@ping(default('i'), observe('j'))
	def do_something(self):
		# do something generic
```

Where the above code would trigger methods decorated with `ping` when the given events occur.

