This was really goofy, but what I did was override the celery base app's `now` to return the proper time, and it started working.  I think this might be a bug in celery 4.1  It's really not that hard to get timezone stuff right celery devs.  

```python
class MyCelery(Celery)
    def now(self):
        """Return the current time and date as a datetime."""
        from datetime import datetime
        return datetime.now(self.timezone)

app = MyCelery()
```

And this fixed the issue for us.

